We define the symmetric Cartan matrix
by requesting that the entry in the i-th row and j-th column
be the scalar product of the i^th and j^th roots. The symmetric Cartan matrix is:
\(\begin{pmatrix}2 & 0 & -1 & 0 & 0 & 0 & 0 & 0\\ 0 & 2 & 0 & -1 & 0 & 0 & 0 & 0\\ -1 & 0 & 2 & -1 & 0 & 0 & 0 & 0\\ 0 & -1 & -1 & 2 & -1 & 0 & 0 & 0\\ 0 & 0 & 0 & -1 & 2 & -1 & 0 & 0\\ 0 & 0 & 0 & 0 & -1 & 2 & -1 & 0\\ 0 & 0 & 0 & 0 & 0 & -1 & 2 & -1\\ 0 & 0 & 0 & 0 & 0 & 0 & -1 & 2\\ \end{pmatrix}\)

Let the (i, j)^{th} entry of the symmetric Cartan matrix be a_{ij}.
Then we define the co-symmetric Cartan matrix as the matrix whose (i, j)^{th} entry equals 4*a_{ij}/(a_{ii}*a_{jj}). In other words, the co-symmetric Cartan matrix is the symmetric Cartan matrix of the dual root system. The co-symmetric Cartan matrix equals:
\(\begin{pmatrix}2 & 0 & -1 & 0 & 0 & 0 & 0 & 0\\ 0 & 2 & 0 & -1 & 0 & 0 & 0 & 0\\ -1 & 0 & 2 & -1 & 0 & 0 & 0 & 0\\ 0 & -1 & -1 & 2 & -1 & 0 & 0 & 0\\ 0 & 0 & 0 & -1 & 2 & -1 & 0 & 0\\ 0 & 0 & 0 & 0 & -1 & 2 & -1 & 0\\ 0 & 0 & 0 & 0 & 0 & -1 & 2 & -1\\ 0 & 0 & 0 & 0 & 0 & 0 & -1 & 2\\ \end{pmatrix}\)
The determinant of the symmetric Cartan matrix is: 1
Half sum of positive roots: (46, 68, 91, 135, 110, 84, 57, 29)= \(-\varepsilon_{2}-2\varepsilon_{3}-3\varepsilon_{4}-4\varepsilon_{5}-5\varepsilon_{6}-6\varepsilon_{7}-23\varepsilon_{8}\)
The fundamental weights (the j^th fundamental weight has scalar product 1
with the j^th simple root times 2 divided by the root length squared,
and 0 with the remaining simple roots):
\(\begin{array}{rcl}(4, 5, 7, 10, 8, 6, 4, 2)&=&-2\varepsilon_{8}\\ (5, 8, 10, 15, 12, 9, 6, 3)&=&-\frac{1}{2}\varepsilon_{1}-\frac{1}{2}\varepsilon_{2}-\frac{1}{2}\varepsilon_{3}-\frac{1}{2}\varepsilon_{4}-\frac{1}{2}\varepsilon_{5}-\frac{1}{2}\varepsilon_{6}-\frac{1}{2}\varepsilon_{7}-\frac{5}{2}\varepsilon_{8}\\ (7, 10, 14, 20, 16, 12, 8, 4)&=&\frac{1}{2}\varepsilon_{1}-\frac{1}{2}\varepsilon_{2}-\frac{1}{2}\varepsilon_{3}-\frac{1}{2}\varepsilon_{4}-\frac{1}{2}\varepsilon_{5}-\frac{1}{2}\varepsilon_{6}-\frac{1}{2}\varepsilon_{7}-\frac{7}{2}\varepsilon_{8}\\ (10, 15, 20, 30, 24, 18, 12, 6)&=&-\varepsilon_{3}-\varepsilon_{4}-\varepsilon_{5}-\varepsilon_{6}-\varepsilon_{7}-5\varepsilon_{8}\\ (8, 12, 16, 24, 20, 15, 10, 5)&=&-\varepsilon_{4}-\varepsilon_{5}-\varepsilon_{6}-\varepsilon_{7}-4\varepsilon_{8}\\ (6, 9, 12, 18, 15, 12, 8, 4)&=&-\varepsilon_{5}-\varepsilon_{6}-\varepsilon_{7}-3\varepsilon_{8}\\ (4, 6, 8, 12, 10, 8, 6, 3)&=&-\varepsilon_{6}-\varepsilon_{7}-2\varepsilon_{8}\\ (2, 3, 4, 6, 5, 4, 3, 2)&=&-\varepsilon_{7}-\varepsilon_{8}\\ \end{array}\)
